translated: Brun, Agnes Hillevi Amalia, high school teacher, Karlshamn, born on August 7th, 1893 in Myssjö, Jämtland, Sweden, daughter of the original and primary school teacher Hugo B. and Amelie Ståhlberg. She graduated from Uppsala with a diploma in 1913 and then received her primary school teaching degree in Gothenburg in 1916. She earned an undergraduate degree in 1920, a graduate degree in 1922 and took a probationary year at Gothenburg's high school in 1926. She traveled to Norway, Denmark, Germany, Austria, Italy, France, Spain, England, Switzerland, and Belgium. She served as a substitute teacher at Avesta primary school in 1916 and as a temporary subject teacher at Varberg in 1929. She became a supervising teacher in Varberg a year later, and since 1938 she has been an adjunct teacher of German, English, and French at Karlshamn's secondary school.

hasOccupation.name: Adjunct teacher of German, English, and French
